[{"id":"/sicp/3.3.1","tag":"TITLE","body":"3.3.1  \n    Mutable List Structure"},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p1","child":[{"body":"\n    The basic operations on\n    \n\tpairs—","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":",\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":",\n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"—can\n    be used to construct list structure and to select parts\n    from list structure, but they are incapable of modifying list\n    structure.  The same is true of the list operations we have used so\n    far, such as ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append"},{"body":" and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"list"},{"body":", since these can be defined in terms of\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":",","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":",\n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":".\n    To modify list structures we need new operations.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p2","child":[{"body":"\n    The primitive mutators for pairs are\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-car!"},{"body":"\n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-cdr!"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Set-car!"},{"body":"\n    takes two arguments, the first of which must be a pair.  It modifies this\n    pair, replacing the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":"\n    pointer by a pointer to the second argument of\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-car!"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-1","body":"1","href":"/sicp/3.3.1#footnote-1"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p3","child":[{"body":"\n    As an example, suppose that ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" is bound to \n    \n\tthe list\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"((a b) c d)"},{"body":"\n    and ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":" to\n    \n\tthe list\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(e f)"},{"body":"\n    as illustrated in\n    \n        figure .\n      \n    Evaluating the expression\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(set-car! x y)"},{"body":"\n    modifies the pair to which ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" is bound,\n    replacing its\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":"\n    by the value of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":".  The result of the operation\n    is shown in\n    \n        figure .\n      \n    The structure ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" has been modified and\n    \n\twould now be printed as\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"((e f) c d)"},{"body":".\n      \n    The pairs representing the list\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(a b)"},{"body":",\n    identified by the pointer that was replaced, are now detached from the\n    original structure.","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-2","body":"2","href":"/sicp/3.3.1#footnote-2"}]},{"tag":"FIGURE","scale":"70%","src":"img_original/ch3-Z-G-13.svg","id":"#fig-","captionHref":"","captionName":"Figure  ","captionBody":[{"body":"\n\t    Lists ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":":\n\t    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"((a b) c d)"},{"body":" and\n\t    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":": ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(e f)"},{"body":".\n          ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"FIGURE","scale":"70%","src":"img_original/ch3-Z-G-14.svg","id":"#fig-","captionHref":"","captionName":"Figure  ","captionBody":[{"body":"\n\t    Effect of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(set-car! x y)"},{"body":" on the lists\n\t    in figure .\n          ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"FIGURE","scale":"70%","src":"img_original/ch3-Z-G-15.svg","id":"#fig-","captionHref":"","captionName":"Figure  ","captionBody":[{"body":"\n\t    Effect of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(define z (cons y (cdr x)))"},{"body":"\n\t    on the lists in figure .\n          ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"FIGURE","scale":"70%","src":"img_original/ch3-Z-G-16.svg","id":"#fig-","captionHref":"","captionName":"Figure  ","captionBody":[{"body":"\n\t    Effect of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(set-cdr! x y)"},{"body":" on the lists\n\t    in figure .\n\t  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p4","child":[{"body":"\n    Compare\n    \n        figure \n    with\n    \n        figure ,\n      \n    which illustrates the result of executing\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":1,"eval":true,"prependLength":4,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xAA8QByTTAQxACMBKEAYxG2eazyNJABPapjL5uGHARJkAXiExsA9sQDOQhW2wAnCt2ZA","body":"(define z (cons y (cdr x))) "},{"body":"\n    with ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" and ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":"\n    bound to the original lists of\n    \n        figure .\n      \n    The\n    \n\tvariable\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"z"},{"body":" is now bound to a\n    new pair created by the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":"\n    operation; the list to which ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" is bound is\n    unchanged.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p5","child":[{"body":"\n    The\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-cdr!"},{"body":"\n    operation is similar to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-car!"},{"body":".\n    The only difference is that the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"\n    pointer of the pair, rather than the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":"\n    pointer, is replaced.  The effect of executing\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(set-cdr! x y)"},{"body":"\n    on the lists of\n    \n        figure \n    is shown in\n    \n        figure .\n      \n    Here the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"\n    pointer of\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" has been replaced by the pointer to\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(e f)"},{"body":".\n    Also, the list\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(c d)"},{"body":",\n    which used to be the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"\n    of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":", is now detached from the structure.\n  ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"TEXT","id":"#p6","child":[{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Cons"},{"body":"\n    builds new list structure by creating new pairs, \n    while ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-car!"},{"body":"\n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"set-cdr!"},{"body":"\n    modify existing pairs.\n    Indeed, we could\n    \n    implement\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":"\n    in terms of the two mutators, together with a\n    procedure","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"get-new-pair"},{"body":",\n    which returns a new pair that is not part of any existing list structure.\n    We obtain the new pair, set its\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"car"},{"body":"\n    and\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"\n    pointers to the designated objects, and return the new pair as the result of\n    the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":".","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"FOOTNOTE_REF","id":"#footnote-link-3","body":"3","href":"/sicp/3.3.1#footnote-3"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":2,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwGMB7YgZxAA8QBPASjRHIBtcAXczKQDu5AOZ8AtMIkAHAIaEATqxUdO5WpIpzFAQhDDG7dRq3Y9B3CLZrOwlUA","body":"(define (cons x y)\n  (let ((new (get-new-pair)))\n    (set-car! new x)\n    (set-cdr! new y)\n    new)) "}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.12","id":"#ex-3.12","child":[{"body":"\n    The following\n    procedure\n    for appending lists was introduced in\n    section ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"2.2.1","href":"/sicp/2.2.1"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":3,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwEMAHK3Y7EADxAE8BKNEcw-c4gVwA2ggPxMOXLi06TMAYwD2xAM7k5FAE7jy1WvTXYtjNqzZm2QA","body":"(define (append x y)\n  (if (null? x)\n    y\n    (cons (car x) (append (cdr x) y)))) "},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"Append"},{"body":"\n    forms a new list by successively\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cons"},{"body":"ing\n\tthe elements of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" onto\n\t","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":".\n      \n    The\n    procedure","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append!"},{"body":"\n    is similar to ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append"},{"body":", but it is a mutator\n    rather than a constructor. It appends the lists by splicing them together,\n    modifying the final pair of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" so that its\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"cdr"},{"body":"\n    is now ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":". (It is an error to call\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append!"},{"body":"\n    with an empty ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":".)\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":4,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwBsBDAZwBcBaABysICcQAPASjRHML5yxAK4UKAfnIBjbBx69+Srn2Xlq9Zqw6ZZ87gd5Y8RUuSpMmuYtgCEXEAE9F5GrkZ77lWoxbsu3E4uamo8QA","body":"(define (append! x y)\n  (set-cdr! (last-pair x) y)\n            x) "},{"body":"\n    Here\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"last-pair"},{"body":"\n    is a\n    procedure\n    that returns the last pair in its argument:\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":5,"eval":true,"prependLength":0,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwBsBDAZwBcBaABysICcQAPASjRHML5yxAK4UKAfnIBjbBx69+Srn2Xlq9Zqw6ZZ87ge5A","body":"(define (last-pair x)\n  (if (null? (cdr x))\n      x\n      (last-pair (cdr x)))) "},{"body":"\n    Consider the interaction\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":6,"eval":true,"prependLength":15,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwEMAHK3Y7EADxAE8BKNEcw-c4gVwA2ggPxMOXLi06TMAYwD2xAM7k5FAE7jy1WvTXYtjNqzZmOWPEVLlBFZQBcAtFQqEjE7r0wDhY+YbinpJMMiGYdo4ubloBHuYYOAQkZJQ0dNgAhEymMpjKuM5yhtkR9s6u7trsYSF1xolWKTkRhI4gAOQUnQBGZkA","body":"(define x (list 'a 'b)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":7,"eval":true,"prependLength":17,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwEMAHK3Y7EADxAE8BKNEcw-c4gVwA2ggPxMOXLi06TMAYwD2xAM7k5FAE7jy1WvTXYtjNqzZmOWPEVLlBFZQBcAtFQqEjE7r0wDhY+YbinpJMMiGYdo4ubloBHuYYOAQkZJQ0dNgAhEymMpjKuM5yhtkR9s6u7trsYSF1xolWKTkRhI4gAOQUnQBGZo3JNiy2bQ6dcp3YZkA","body":"(define y (list 'c 'd)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":8,"eval":true,"prependLength":19,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwEMAHK3Y7EADxAE8BKNEcw-c4gVwA2ggPxMOXLi06TMAYwD2xAM7k5FAE7jy1WvTXYtjNqzZmOWPEVLlBFZQBcAtFQqEjE7r0wDhY+YbinpJMMiGYdo4ubloBHuYYOAQkZJQ0dNgAhEymMpjKuM5yhtkR9s6u7trsYSF1xolWKTkRhI4gAOQUnQBGZo3JNiy2bQ6dcp3Y-ZaDZABeOun6zOxsQA","body":"(define z (append x y)) "},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":9,"eval":true,"prependLength":21,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygk