onse"},{"body":"s?\n    Draw box-and-pointer diagrams to explain your answer.\n    ","tag":"#text"}],"solution":[{"body":"\n      The first response is ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"[\"b\", null]"},{"body":" and the second is\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"[\"b\", [\"c\", [\"d\", null]]]"},{"body":".\n\n      The function ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append"},{"body":" builds a new list by copying the pairs of\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" and making the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"tail"},{"body":" of the last copied pair refer to\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":". Only the pairs holding ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"\"a\""},{"body":" and\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"\"b\""},{"body":" are freshly created; the result ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"z"},{"body":" shares its\n      last two pairs ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"[\"c\", [\"d\", null]]"},{"body":" with ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":".\n      Since ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append"},{"body":" does not modify ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":", the value of\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"tail(x)"},{"body":" is still ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"[\"b\", null]"},{"body":".\n\n      The function ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"append_mutator"},{"body":", by contrast, splices the lists\n      together by setting the ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"tail"},{"body":" of the last pair of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" to\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":", mutating ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":" itself. After\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"const w = append_mutator(x, y);"},{"body":" the value of ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"tail(x)"},{"body":" is\n      therefore ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"[\"b\", [\"c\", [\"d\", null]]]"},{"body":", and\n      ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"x"},{"body":", ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"w"},{"body":", and ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"y"},{"body":" now share structure.\n    ","tag":"#text"}]},{"tag":"EXERCISE","title":"Exercise 3.13","id":"#ex-3.13","child":[{"body":"\n    Consider the following\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"make-cycle"},{"body":"procedure,\n    which uses the\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"last-pair"},{"body":"procedure\n    defined in exercise ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"REF","body":"3.12","href":"/sicp/3.3.1#ex-3.12"},{"body":":\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":14,"eval":true,"prependLength":6,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwBsBDAZwBcBaABysICcQAPASjRHML5yxAK4UKAfnIBjbBx69+Srn2Xlq9Zqw6ZZ87gd5Y8RUuQC2VANa4G0gJ7SKZHqsw1cjPQEJ1tRizsXNzBqmpqrsYEJGQAXhbWtg5OZJSE9CAA5FRZAEZZ0oZAA","body":"(define (make-cycle x)\n  (set-cdr! (last-pair x) x)\n            x) "},{"body":"\n    Draw a box-and-pointer diagram that shows the structure\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"z"},{"body":" created by\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SNIPPET","latex":false,"id":15,"eval":true,"prependLength":10,"program":"chap=3&prgrm=NwAgygkgwgCiDMA6JBGAUGgFAEwKYDMBLAO1xEwBsBDAZwBcBaABysICcQAPASjRHML5yxAK4UKAfnIBjbBx69+Srn2Xlq9Zqw6ZZ87gd5Y8RUuQC2VANa4G0gJ7SKZHqsw1cjPQEJ1tRizsXNzBqmpqrsYEJGQAXhbWtg5OZJSE9CAA5FRZAEZZ0oZAA","body":"(define z (make-cycle (list 'a 'b 'c))) "},{"body":"\n    What happens if we try to compute\n    ","tag":"#text"},{"tag":"SCHEMEINLINE","body":"(last-pair z)"},{"body":"?","tag":"#text"}],"solution":[{"body":"\n      (provided by GitHub user jonathantorres)\n      I